1. Introduction

This project was developed as part of the BYOP (Bring Your Own Project) in the Fundamentals of AI & ML course.
The main goal was to get a basic understanding of how machine learning works in a practical scenario, rather than just theory.

2. Problem Statement

Many students feel uncertain about their placement chances.
They often don’t know how factors like CGPA, study habits, and internships actually affect their outcomes, which can lead to confusion and poor planning.

3. Objective

The objective of this project is to build a simple machine learning model that can predict whether a student is likely to get placed based on a few key inputs.

4. Methodology

To complete this project, I followed a simple approach:

Created a small dataset manually
Selected important features like CGPA, study hours, and internship experience
Used a Logistic Regression model for prediction
Built a basic user interface using Streamlit

This step-by-step approach helped me understand the complete workflow of an ML project.

5. Dataset

Since this is a beginner-level project, I created a small dataset myself.
It includes:

CGPA
Study hours
Internship (yes/no)
Placement status

Even though the dataset is small, it was enough to demonstrate how a machine learning model works.

6. Model Used

I used Logistic Regression for this project because it is simple and suitable for binary classification problems like predicting placement (placed or not placed).

7. Implementation

The project was implemented using:

Python for coding
Pandas for handling data
Scikit-learn for building the ML model
Streamlit for creating a simple interactive UI

The user can enter their details and instantly get a prediction.

8. Results

The model is able to give predictions based on the input values.
Since the dataset is small, the accuracy is not very high, but the main goal of understanding how ML works has been achieved.

9. Challenges Faced

While working on this project, I faced a few challenges:

Understanding how to structure the dataset properly
Fixing file naming and path errors
Connecting the machine learning model with the Streamlit interface

These challenges helped me learn practical problem-solving.

10. Conclusion

This project gave me a clear idea of how machine learning can be applied to a simple real-world problem.
It also helped me understand the full process—from data to model to user interface.

11. Future Improvements

In the future, this project can be improved by:

Using a larger and more realistic dataset
Improving model accuracy
Adding more features like skills, projects, etc.
Making the UI more advanced and user-friendly
